# Documentation audit ignore file
#
# Purpose:
# Keep Git tracking separate from architecture-document audit scope.
# Paths listed here are still tracked by Git unless also listed in .gitignore.
#
# Pattern rules:
# - Blank lines and lines starting with # are ignored.
# - A trailing slash marks a directory or path prefix.
# - A path containing / is matched as a repository-relative prefix.
# - A bare name is matched against any path segment or filename.

